burlap.behavior.stochasticgames.madynamicprogramming

Interface QSourceForSingleAgent

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MADynamicProgramming.BackupBasedQSource, QSourceForSingleAgent.HashBackedQSource

    public interface QSourceForSingleAgent
    And interface for objects that can store and retrive Q-value objects for a specific agent and state and joint action query. The JAQValue returned can have their q datamember directly modified to modify the Q-values stored and retreived in this object. A hash-backed implementation is also provided in this interface definition.
    Author:
    James MacGlashan

    • Nested Class Summary

      An implementation of the QSourceForSingleAgent interface that has Q-values backed by hashmaps.

    • Method Detail

      • getQValueFor

        JAQValue getQValueFor(State s,
                      JointAction ja)
        Returns a Q-value (represented with a JAQValue object) stored for the given state and joint action. Modification to the returned object will directly modify the stored value that will be returned in subsequent calls to this method.
        Parameters:
        s - the Q-value's associated state
        ja - the Q-value's associated joint aciton
        Returns:
        a JAQValue for the given state and joint action.
